The Registration fee varies from $500 - $2,500 per item.  The time for
registration also varies - from 6 weeks to 1.5 years - depending on the
complexity of the equipment.  Existing regulations have created a long and
bureaucratic registration process which is causing some companies to
circumvent the process, sometimes illegally.  Companies with a highly
regarded and reliable local partner have the most success in finding
legitimate avenues to speed up the registration process.

As this process has proven to be particularly painful, demand for better
service is increasing and a certification laboratory will be opening soon in
St. Petersburg.  The founders of this laboratory include: the Russian
Ministry of Health, Rosstandart (Russian Committee on Standardization) and
the Institute of Preventive Medicine (St. Petersburg).  For further
information please contact:

